  "text": "+ GFP -cells were sorted from pooled LN (axillary, cervical, inguinal, mesenteric, pancreatic and pelvic para-aortal) and spleen cells [CITATION_1] , activated with anti-CD3 (2C11)/anti-CD28 (PV-1) mAbs (0.5 mg/ml each) with 20 ng/ml human recombinant TGF-b (R&D). Retinoic acid (Sigma Aldrich R2625) diluted in DMSO (Sigma Aldrich) was added at 2.5 nM final concentration. After 4 or 5 days cells were harvested, washed, counted and stained with mAb anti-CD4 Alexa647 (clone GK1.5), then purified with a MoFlo cell sorter into GFP 2 and GFP + CD4 + T cells.",
